cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper deals with randomized experiments in web-based services, which involves analyzing user behavior and data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves data analysis and statistical frameworks, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with clustering and graph theory, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
